        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: add retention purge command",
        "body": "Fixes #47.\n\n## Summary\n\n- add `slacrawl purge` with exactly one of `--before` or `--older-than`\n- preview by default; require `--force` for deletion and `--force --vacuum` for compaction\n- support optional workspace scoping and `--keep-media`\n- delete message-owned rows transactionally and clean unreferenced cached media under a cross-process cache lock\n- record retention floors so routine API, MCP, tail, and repair ingestion cannot silently restore purged history\n\n## Retention model\n\n- cutoff is exclusive\n- posted threads use the parent timestamp, so an expired root and all replies are removed together\n- desktop drafts use their own timestamp/update time and remain independent of thread age\n- exact/full historical syncs, an explicitly older `--since`, desktop ingestion, and imports may restore purged data\n- normal incremental reads clamp to the retention floor; API uses an inclusive boundary and MCP requests one microsecond before the floor while retaining write-time filtering\n\n## Safety\n\n- database deletion is one transaction\n- retention-aware writes reserve the SQLite writer before checking floors, preventing snapshot races\n- previews use a read-only database snapshot and do not reserve the writer\n- force-mode media deletion rechecks references under `BEGIN IMMEDIATE`\n- media path checks are case-insensitive to protect shared physical files on macOS and Windows\n- failed orphan cleanup is retried by later purges\n- legacy truncated desktop draft IDs are migrated during ingestion\n\n## Proof\n\n- `GOWORK=off go test -count=1 ./...`\n- `GOWORK=off go vet ./...`\n- `GOWORK=off go test -race -count=1 ./internal/store ./internal/media ./internal/cli ./internal/share ./internal/slackapi ./internal/slackmcp ./internal/slackdesktop`\n- `GOWORK=off go run golang.org/x/tools/cmd/deadcode@v0.45.0 -test ./...`\n- Windows cross-compile: media and share packages\n- CLI build and `purge --help` smoke test\n- autoreview: clean, no accepted/actionable findings\n\nNo release is included.\n",
